description: Permanently deletes a SizeConstraintSet. You can't delete a SizeConstraintSet if it's still used in any Rules or if it still includes any SizeConstraint objects (any filters). If you just want to remove a SizeConstraintSet from a Rule, use UpdateRule. To permanently delete a SizeConstraintSet, perform the following steps:   Update the SizeConstraintSet to remove filters, if any. For more information, see UpdateSizeConstraintSet.   Use GetChangeToken to get the change token that you provide in the ChangeToken parameter of a DeleteSizeConstraintSet request.   Submit a DeleteSizeConstraintSet request.
